      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOSTON STRONG (2) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Major Impact (22.96) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Rates highly and will give a great sight. TINY SNIFFY (1) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (29.70) at The Gardens behind Larrikin Pioneer in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Goes well out of this box with a win and five minor placings. Can measure up. ARTICULATE (8) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when eighth at this track over 401m behind Dennis Keeping (23.43) in a Grade 4/5. Was a winner prior to that. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. A big run wouldn't surprise. ZIPPING LUMIERE (3) can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
